title: The Gunsmith Handbook [blackatk]
description:
Publication Date: July 6, 2013
From basic disassembly and maintenance to more complex repair and customization techniques, weapons expert B. Smith explains in clear text and detailed photos how to get the very most out of your pistol or revolver. Whether you're wondering how to mount a front or rear sight, replace a cylinder, give your gun a thorough cleaning or perform any one of a hundred other essential procedures, you'll find it in this latest edition of The Gunsmith Handbook.

The book also contains several illustrations that will be sure to guide you in the most complex of situations.


Author: B. Smith
Print Length: 228 pages
Language: English
